&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Naval:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The value is in the knowledge, and the knowledge is inside the observer and the creator, in other words, a human. It&amp;rsquo;s not inside the thing itself. For example, oil is useless unless you know how to refine it, burn it, and use it for combustion. Information is useless unless there&amp;rsquo;s a brain there to receive it.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>It’s Impossible to Predict the Growth of Knowledge</title><link>https://linguista.cn/naval/orig/its-impossible-to-predict-the-growth-of-knowledge/</link><pubDate>Fri, 19 Mar 2021 18:23:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://linguista.cn/naval/orig/its-impossible-to-predict-the-growth-of-knowledge/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://linguista.cn/naval/zh/its-impossible-to-predict-the-growth-of-knowledge.zh/"&gt;中文版本&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
