&lt;h1 id="being-a-noob"&gt;Being a Noob&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;January 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When I was young, I thought old people had everything figured out. Now that I&amp;rsquo;m old, I know this isn&amp;rsquo;t true.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I constantly feel like a noob. It seems like I&amp;rsquo;m always talking to some startup working in a new field I know nothing about, or reading a book about a topic I don&amp;rsquo;t understand well enough, or visiting some new country where I don&amp;rsquo;t know how things work.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>How to Get New Ideas</title><link>https://linguista.cn/paul_graham/essays_en/getideas/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://linguista.cn/paul_graham/essays_en/getideas/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;→ &lt;a href="https://linguista.cn/paul_graham/essays_zh/getideas/"&gt;中文版本&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
