&lt;h1 id="how-you-know"&gt;How You Know&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;December 2014&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I&amp;rsquo;ve read Villehardouin&amp;rsquo;s chronicle of the Fourth Crusade at least two times, maybe three. And yet if I had to write down everything I remember from it, I doubt it would amount to much more than a page. Multiply this times several hundred, and I get an uneasy feeling when I look at my bookshelves. What use is it to read all these books if I remember so little from them?&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>The illustrated guide to a Ph.D.</title><link>https://linguista.cn/terencetao/career-advice/orig/the-illustrated-guide-to-a-phd/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://linguista.cn/terencetao/career-advice/orig/the-illustrated-guide-to-a-phd/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://linguista.cn/terencetao/career-advice/zh/the-illustrated-guide-to-a-phd.zh/"&gt;中文版本&lt;/a&gt;
